  "text": "Scintigraphic evaluation of the heart for uptake of radiolabeled phosphonates by amyloid was first explored more than 20 years ago. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Sensitivity for diagnosis has been variable; thus, the test has not been incorporated into the routine workup for cardiac amyloidosis. [CITATION_3] A recent study, however, indicates that technetium Tc 99m-3,3,-diphosphono-1,2-propanodicarboxylic acid may be capable of differentiating TTR-associated amyloidosis from AL amyloidosis.",
